  "prompt": "Are there any antibiotics that can be purchased over the counter?",
  "response": "In the United States, antibiotics are not available over the counter and require a prescription from a healthcare provider. This is to ensure that the antibiotics are used appropriately and effectively, as misuse can lead to antibiotic resistance. However, there are some topical antibiotics, like Neosporin or Polysporin, that can be purchased over the counter for minor skin infections. \n\nIn some other countries, certain antibiotics may be available over the counter, but it's always best to consult with a healthcare professional before starting any new medication.",
